Bremed BD 5200 Nebulizer
Description: The Bremed BD 5200 Nebulizer is an ultra-sonic inhaler and an ideal device for the treatment of all respiratory and lung related conditions. This nebulizer uses its ultra-sonic power to break down the curative solution into small aerosol droplets that can be breathed directly from the mouthpiece. The ultra-sonic nebulizer is designed with a separate motor speed and nebulization flow speed which enhances the performance of the device. Simple and compact this nebulizer from Bremed allows the precise dosage of medicine to reach your lungs. Body The Bremed BD 5200 Nebulizer can be used by both adults and children since the device consists of an adult mask as well as the pediatric mask. Along with the masks, the main unit also comprises of an angled mouth piece, a medicinal cup and a set of five spare replaceable filters. Weighing 210 g, the Bremed BD 5200 Nebulizer can be carried along while you are on the move. In addition to this, the device also comes with a smart nylon pouch, making it all the more easier for you to carry. The medication cup which is connected to the mouthpiece is capable of holding 4 ml of the medicinal solution, helping you breathe with ease. The Bremed BD 5200 Nebulizer has dimensions of 12.9 cm x 6.9 cm x 5.2 cm. Performance and Features This nebulizer from Bremed delivers adequate amount of medication to your lungs at an average nebulization rate 1 ml per minute. The ultra-sonic nebulizer produces a particle size of 0.5 to 4 μm, hence making it possible for the tiny particles to travel through the narrow branches of your lower airways. The Bremed BD 5200 Nebulizer operates swiftly at a temperature ranging from 10 to 40 degree Celsius and humidity ranging from 30 to 85% RH. You can store the nebulizer at a temperature ranging from 20 to 60 degree Celsius with a humidity ranging from 10 to 95% RH. This nebulizer machine uses electricity with a power supply of 100 - 240V 50-60 Hz. The device consumes only 16 W of power supply and also comes with an option of operating on batteries ( to be bought separately) . These batteries could be recharged with the adaptor that comes along with this nebulizer.
